[{"id":"VR914718","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram of an incident light beam moving to the right towards glass blocks, labeled Glass Block 1 and Glass Block 2. The glass blocks are on a flat surface, and there is an air gap between the blocks. Glass Block 1 has antireflection coating on the left surface. Glass Block 2 has antireflection coating on the right surface. A note states that the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR914718.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A beam of light of wavelength <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"480 nanometers\"><math alttext=\"480 nanometers\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>480</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>nm</mtext></math></span></span> in air is incident on a setup consisting of two blocks of glass that are separated by a narrow air gap, as shown in the figure. There are antireflection coatings on both the left surface of Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and the right surface of Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, so that <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"100 percent\"><math alttext=\"100 percent\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>100</mn><mi>%</mi></math></span></span> of any incident light is always transmitted at these surfaces. Both blocks have a refractive index of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1.50\"><math alttext=\"1.50\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1.50</mn></math></span></span>. What is the thinnest nonzero air gap that results in the maximum amount of light being transmitted through the two blocks?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR914718_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"80 nanometers\"><math alttext=\"80 nanometers\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>80</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>nm</mtext></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"120 nanometers\"><math alttext=\"120 nanometers\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>120</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>nm</mtext></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"160 nanometers\"><math alttext=\"160 nanometers\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>160</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>nm</mtext></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"240 nanometers\"><math alttext=\"240 nanometers\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>240</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>nm</mtext></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":3}]